dymo-web-service (0.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * HTTPS served via LibreSSL's native libtls API in a dedicated thread.
    The previous mongoose OpenSSL-compat path fragmented the TLS
    handshake into tiny TCP segments, which tripped the DYMO framework's
    XHR state machine on CellarTracker. libtls writes directly to the
    socket fd and matches the on-wire behaviour of uvicorn / mainstream
    servers.
  * Mongoose is now built with MG_TLS=MG_TLS_NONE; it is used only for
    the plain-HTTP listener on port 41951. The mongoose BIO patch is no
    longer applied.

 -- loadfix <noreply@anthropic.com>  Tue, 29 Apr 2026 21:30:00 +0000

dymo-web-service (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial C port of the Python dymo_service.
  * Bundles mongoose (HTTP) and LibreSSL (TLS, static).
  * Cairo+Pango rendering, libqrencode for QR, hand-rolled ITF/Code128.

